gomodel:SYNGO_1969  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig.2: Electrophysiological Tag of NMDA-R Allows Monitoring of Functional Insertion of Recombinant Receptor into Synapses.\n\nNote: The tagging technique uses over-expression of a mutant form of NR1 with slightly altered channel properties that allows detection of the participation of NMDA channels containing this subunit in synaptic transmission.. Experimental description: - Species of the over-expressed protein is not stated in the paper. Authors were contacted (rmalinow@ucsd.edu, barria@uw.edu, dd 24/11/2017). Authors answered:\n\n\"HI,\nYes, in both papers (Barria & Malinow, Neuron 2002 and 2005) the receptors are from rat.\nThe original clones were obtained from Nakanishi's lab or Mishina's lab via Yasunori Hayashi.\nAt some point I fully sequenced them and they are a match with the rat sequence deposited in NCBI\n\nCheers\nAndres\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0593-3443" ;
        dc:date           "2017-11-29" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_MF_1969" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

